ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend this course to any student interested in the history of cities if they are up for the work.
Yes, listen to everything that Jay and John have to say about anything, and you will be a better scholar, and perhaps a better person, for it.

Fantastic course... multidimensional and interdisciplinary approach to comparative urban history... I enjoyed the various subjects we looked at (f.ex. representationss of the 2 cities in art and litterature, the questions of urban planning, cities at war etc.)I highly recommend the course!

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I'm learning new ways to ask questions and new means of finding answers. The angle of my attack for cultural history is sharpening.
